article.headline: Robert Morris 45, St. Francis (Pa.) 14
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Jeff Sinclair threw three touchdown passes and ran for two more scores, leading Robert Morris in a 45-14 rout over St. Francis (Pa.) on Saturday night. Sinclair was 10 of 15 for 155 yards with an interception, adding 110 yards on five carries for the Colonials (2-3, 2-0 Northeast Conference). Robert Morris now leads the all-time series 15-2-1, and has won the last six meetings against the Red Flash. The Robert Morris quarterback had touchdown passes of 24 and 16 yards to Shadrae King, as well as a scoring connection of 25 yards to Jamar Cromwell in the first half. He also added TD runs of 64 and 22 yards, sparking the Colonials to a 35-0 halftime lead. King, the reigning NEC offensive player of the week, finished with 66 yards on four catches. Cory Nielsen threw for 150 yards, two TDs and two interceptions for St. Francis (1-5, 0-4).
